utput of the AGN and the non-gravitational dispersion. It is not possible to\nuniquely determine the BH mass for each galaxy from its nuclear gas dispersion.\nHowever, for the sample as a whole the observed dispersions do not provide\nevidence for significant deviations from the M-sigma relation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 2 Jan 2006 09:20:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-11"}
